-- Red Bull’s Vettel Claims Pole Position for Canadian Grand Prix
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-06-09T18:35:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-09/red-bull-s-vettel-claims-pole-position-for-canadian-grand-prix.html
Red Bull’s Sebastian Vettel claimed
his second pole position of the Formula One season by topping
qualifying for tomorrow’s Canadian Grand Prix.  Vettel, the two-time defending world champion, beat
McLaren’s Lewis Hamilton by three-tenths of a second at the
Circuit Gilles Villeneuve in Montreal. It’s the German’s second
straight pole in Canada and 32nd of his career.  Ferrari’s  Fernando Alonso , who leads the season standings,
will start on row two next to Red Bull’s  Mark Webber . Nico
Rosberg of Mercedes, Ferrari’s Felipe Massa, Lotus’s Romain
Grosjean, Force India’s Paul di Resta, Mercedes’s Michael
Schumacher and Jenson Button of McLaren round out the top-10
qualifiers.  Six different drivers have won the first six races of the
season.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  